# Public Pages Rules

## Scope

Applies to all routes under `app/` that are **not** under `app/admin/`. This includes home (`app/page.tsx`), services (`app/services/`), book (`app/book/`), find-us, blog, terms, privacy, gdpr, etc.

## Server vs Client

- **Server components (default):** No `"use client"`. Use for static content, fetching data in the component, and `generateMetadata`. Example: `app/page.tsx`, many layout files.
- **Client components:** Add `"use client"` at the top when the page uses hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs. Example: booking flow pages, forms, pages that use `useState`/`useEffect`.

## Metadata

- Export `generateMetadata` for SEO when the page is server-rendered:
  ```typescript
  export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
    return {
      title: "Page Title | EGP Aesthetics",
      description: "...",
    };
  }
  ```
- Use `metadataBase` from root layout; relative paths in Open Graph images are resolved against it.

## Layout

- Public pages are wrapped by `LayoutMain` (from root layout), which includes `HeaderAesthetics`, `FloatingContactButtons`, `FooterAesthetics`, and optional `DayOffBanner`.
- Main content has top padding to clear the fixed header (`pt-[90px]` or `pt-[100px]` when day-off banner is shown).
- Do not add a second full-width header/footer; use the existing layout.

## Typography & Containers

- Use `typography.headingPage` or `typography.headingSection` for page/section titles (from `@/config/typography`).
- Use `layout.container` or `layout.containerNarrow` for content width and padding.
- Use `layout.sectionPy` for section vertical spacing.

## Data Fetching

- Server components: fetch directly or use async server functions; can use `createClient()` from `lib/supabase/server` for server-only data.
- Client components: use hooks that call `/api/*` (e.g. `useServices`, `useReviews`). Do not call Supabase from the client.

## Dynamic Routes

- `app/services/[slug]/page.tsx` — service detail by slug
- `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` — blog post by slug
- `app/conditions/[slug]/page.tsx` — condition page by slug
- Use `params` in the page (and in `generateMetadata` if needed); in Next.js 15+ params may be a Promise.

## Don'ts

- Do not add admin-only logic or `requireAdmin()` on public pages
- Do not expose internal API keys or service role; only call public or admin-protected API routes from the client as intended
